{"article_id":"SMSSP0gTAqeYpJA2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The US economy added 223,00 jobs in April","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"The unemployment rate fell to 5.4 percent .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Economists had expected 230,000 jobs and a 5.4 percent unemployment rate ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"so this is basically right on target .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The two previous months ' jobs reports were revised downward ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"removing 39,000 jobs .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"Really the only unusual or exciting thing about this jobs report is how unusual it is for something so thoroughly expected and non-game-changing to happen .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Adding a bit over 200,000 jobs a month is both what","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"analysts thought would happen ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"and also a trajectory","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"that is consistent with a continued slow decline in unemployment but no real labor market boom .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Dive deeper into the data ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"and the basic lack of surprises only continues .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Labor force participation is up , but only very slightly .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Hourly wages are up , but only very slightly .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"There 's nothing about this jobs report","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"that is likely to change the Federal Reserve 's mind about anything ,","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"and therefore no reason","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"to expect financial markets to have any particular reaction .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"Those","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"who think","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"the Fed 's current course is dangerously inflationary","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"will keep thinking that .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Those","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"who","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"( more correctly ! )","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"think","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"the Fed 's current course is unreasonably inflation-averse","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"will keep thinking that , as well .","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"Janet Yellen will keep thinking","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"she 's on the right track .","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"Monthly wage growth update :","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"meh edition pic.twitter.com/o5zGiZe8Tw","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"- Nick Bunker","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"( @ nick_bunker )","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"May 8 , 2015","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"Wage growth appears to have settled into a steady pattern","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that is somewhat better than what we saw at the depths of the recession ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"but far below what was considered normal before the recession .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Partially offsetting this ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"overall consumer price inflation has been abnormally low for a couple of years now .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"There are also some compositional effects","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"pulling average wages down","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"as a large cohort of inexperienced 20-somethings have been entering the workforce .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"Overall it is a little difficult to understand why some of the small upward bumps have been interpreted in some quarters as a sign of an imminent inflationary breakout .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Even the strongest wage-growth months have been weak","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"compared with 2006 or 2007 , years","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"that were not exactly halcyon days for the American worker .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Perhaps the clearest sign","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"of how not-yet-completed America 's recovery","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"comes from looking at the level of full-time jobs ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"which is still well below where it was in 2007 :","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"US has added 7.9 million full-time jobs","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"since recession ended","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"but there are still 750,000 fewer than when it began","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"pic.twitter.com/YKTeuzeXK","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"2 - Nick Timiraos","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"( @ NickTimiraos )","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"May 8 , 2015","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"The population ,","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"needless to say ,","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"has grown in the intervening years ,","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"meaning that the failure","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"to fully catch up in job growth","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"makes it difficult for rank-and-file workers to gain bargaining leverage .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":131,"left":97,"right":130,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":81,"right":96,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":81,"left":72,"right":80,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":72,"left":70,"right":71,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":68,"right":69,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":68,"left":67,"right":2,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":67,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":69,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":71,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":80,"left":76,"right":79,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":76,"left":7,"right":75,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":73,"right":74,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":73,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":79,"left":77,"right":78,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"pa